rComments: An amazIng prof. I was fortunate enough to be on the field camp with Marc where he made me laugh to the point that I almost peed myself. Super inspirational and knows exactly what he's talking about. Will answer any questions, and is there to make sure students feel comfortable.

Best teacher I ever had. You can see that he cares for his students and he would explain you a thousand times if you don't understand something. He has so much experience and knowledge, which can be felt when he is teaching.

Lectures and readings were generally interesting. The marking consisted of 4 tests and a Final. The wording on tests was chosen to be confusing (he would not use terminology used in lectures/readings on tests) which often made it difficult to understand what he was looking for.

J'ai passé le cours de Mr. Brosseau avec la sueur de mon front. Il était très vague dans l'explication de ses concepts, il parle vite et il a la tendance à ne pas être spécifique. Par contre, il est spécifique dans ses attentes d'examen et du travail de groupe. J'ai passé ce cours avec les doigts croisés.

I would advise you to stay from this professor at all cost. Thoroughly enjoys seeing students in pain and refuses to admit that he is flawed in the way he teaches/grades/communicates with students. Despises criticism, so dont even try. Just another white privileged prof with a huge ego who thinks they can do anything & say anything.
Le cours est intéressant et n'a pas été donné depuis longtemps... Les critères ne sont pas toujours claires, mais super cours a prendre si vous voulez prendre ça relaxe, mais tout de même apprendre.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Très bon professeur. Il connait sa matière, mais si vous ne voulez pas étudier des espaces sous-tension qui ne sont pas internationaux, ce n'est pas le cours pour vous. Les cours sont relativement simple, mais il faut écouter parce que ses tests sont sur la matière.

Le contenu du cours est assez ennuyant mais ce professeur est clairement passionné. Il a tendance à avancer très lentement dans les diapos, il n'y donc pas beaucoup de matière à étudier à la fin. Je suggère d'aller aux cours précédent les examens; il donne pratiquement toutes les questions. La correction des examens est assez sévère, attention.

Un prof fantastique!! J'ai adoré son cours. C'était super intéressant, il explique super bien les concepts, et a choisi des thèmes très intéressants. Le travail de session est difficile mais très cool. Il est toujours disponible pour des questions, et très sympa!

Marc est un excellent pédagogue/professeur à l'Université d'Ottawa. Certainement, un des meilleurs professeurs au département de géographie. Il est très savant et sa passion pour le domaine se transmet au travers de son enseignement. Il apporte toujours une attitude positive à ses cours. Il est important de bien écouter dans ses cours!

Très drôle, je l'ai vraiment aimé. Le cours te permet d'apprendre vraiment. C'est un cours qui donne une bonne connaissance générale dans tout les domaines d'études. le seul bémol c'est qu'il est très abstrait dans la plupart de ses explications.
Le cours est très intéressant et il est prêt à aider. Les examens sont difficiles et les projets aussi, mais il suffit de bien étudier la matière.

Il est chouette, il connaît bien sa matière, mais parfois il s'égare en parlant!! Ce n'est pas ma matière préférée, mais ce n'est pas la faute du prof, c'est juste un mauvais choix que j'ai fait!! C'est un bon prof, mais étudiez car ses examens sont difficiles sans étude!!!
Professeur inspirant pouvant amener ses étudiants à un autre niveau. Je vous recommande tous les cours qu'il enseigne.

Attendance isn't mandated, but it is definitely extremely, absolutely 100% helpful. This man created this course and is using a novel he (along with others from the Geography department) wrote about the Ottawa-Gatineau border. Only one major project; super awesome for French Imm students. Course material: 50$+18.50$ approximately, no rent option

Marc is an amazing individual and such a laid-back professor. I'm taking both GEG1702 and GEG2508 with him (French courses); the textbook is basically your go-to, but he explains everything in his lectures so thoroughly that it's almost unnecessary (but still expected). Not many assignments at all. Very approachable. Psyched for GEG2508 in Winter.
Really interesting class. Fair marker.

He's nice and all, but not my favorite prof. He makes the subject interesting, but the objective of his final paper was very unclear. He's very hard on correction too. The course pack isnt necessary and he posts his slides online.

Great course, loved the material, but I had one major issue and that was his attitude towards francophones that live outside of Quebec, particularly Franco-Ontarians. He made comments that were belittling this group and it made me feel uncomfortable considering that he is teaching in an Ontario university to Franco-Ontarians like me. I take offense
Best prof I've ever had.. interesting, funny, and willing to help you out when needed. Also very accepting/ willing to help french immersion students

Excellent professeur qui connait bien son sujet. Si vous prenez des notes et faites les lectures vous allez réussir. Les cas d'étude ont été très intéressants et j'ai appris beaucoup dans ce cours. Même comme étudiant en immersion j'ai très bien réussi dans ce cours.  Si vous prenez ce cours vous ne le regretterez jamais.

I personally think this course is a waste of time. For field camp, you are basically paying $1,100 (PLUS lunches) to go to montreal. He did not give us ANY information about the course until a week before the course started. Half of the course pack is in French...with no english equivalents. Gotta love buying a book you can only read half of.

He is an extremely passionate professor teaching the class that he created. The course is extremely straight forward. He even underlines the key concepts of the course for you. The text for the class is a collection of articles that helps understand the cases but the class can easily be aced with attendance and note taking. Recommended

I enjoyed the class, and I thought he was a great teacher. Extremely helpful, especially being in immersion in his class. He CREATED this course and so is extremely passionate about it. I found it a bit disorganized, other than that loved it.

Good prof, liked the class. only thing that detracted from it was he seemed to kind of skip steps at points, probably because he does this stuff all the time and they seem obvious to him, overall though very good prof and tries hard to make sure you do well.
I loved the first part of the course taught by this prof. Well organized, and if you go to class, you will know EXACTLY what to expect on her midterm and her part of the final.

Ce prof-là est génial. Très sympathique, clair, précis. Il répond à toutes les questions, vulgarise bien et ses notes sont très faciles à comprendre. Il est passionné par son domaine et il nous donne le goût d'en savoir plus! A++++

Words can not describe how amazing this prof is. If every class were like his, no one would complain about the cost of tuition because they'd know they were getting a bargain. Recommended to anyone and everyone.

Je n'avais pas le gout de prendre le cours, mais je le reprendrais toute ma vie tellement c'était intéressant.  Les travaux sont claires, les examens faciles si vous assistez au cours.  Le prof est full bon!
coolest teacher I've ever had.
He's a hottie. He also teaches very well!!
cutie
